author: @carlitosss-h2h
text_translated: the nintendo switch 2 system can adapt to suit your situation however you like to play in tv mode use the dock to play on a bigger screen in tabletop mode place your system however you like using the stand and share a controller with a friend in handheld mode play anywhere you go with these three play modes you can enjoy playing whenever and wherever you want altogether anytime anywhere lets take a look at some features of nintendo switch 2 and how its improved from the nintendo switch system at 79 inches switch 2 has a bigger builtin screen heres how that compares to nintendo switch the systems thickness remains the same with approximately double the pixels compared to switch you can enjoy games in greater detail on the 1080p screen the screen supports up to 120 frames per second allowing for smoother gameplay in supported titles the lcd screen is more vivid and supports hdr providing more contrast between light and dark areas of the images the all new joycon 2 controllers connect magnetically strong magnets keep the controllers firmly attached to the system dettach a controller easily by pressing the release button on the back the sl and sr buttons are bigger for greater comfort and control when playing with a joycon 2 held horizontally the left and right sticks are now larger each joycon 2 controller can be used as a mouse opening up even more ways to play in compatible games both the left and right joycon 2s support mouse controls so you can also play certain games using two mice like this by adjusting the audio balance between the ranges sounds from the builtin speakers are clearer and more natural in handheld and tabletop modes it has a builtin microphone so you can voice chat with friends anytime via gamechat it also uses voice cancelling technology to filter sound so your voice will come through clearly even if you dont have a surround sound system games can be enjoyed with more immersive threedimensional sound as if it were coming from all around you place your nintendo switch 2 however you like with a large sturdy stand you can move it freely like this in addition to the usbc port found on the bottom of the system theres one on top as well its handy for connecting a usbc camera or charging in tabletop mode nintendo switch 2 comes with 256gb of internal storage eight times that of nintendo switch for storing your game downloads save data and more reading and writing data is also faster use the nintendo switch 2 dock to connect to your tv and enable up to 4k resolution for compatible games hdr is also supported in tv mode the nintendo switch 2 dock has a builtin fan that keeps your system cool this helps keep performance stable on nintendo switch 2 you can play nintendo switch 2 games as well as compatible nintendo switch games physical and digital games are supported

author: @LF420-l7o
text_translated: actually for those who dont know mario is a character created by the japanese game designer shigeru miyamoto he is the star of the mario franchise a recurring character in the donkey kong franchise and the mascot of the japanese video game company nintendo mario is an italian plumber who lives in the mushroom kingdom with his younger twin brother luigi their adventures generally involve rescuing princess peach from the villain bowser while using powerups that give them different abilities marios distinctive characteristics include his large nose and mustache overalls red cap and highpitched exaggerated italian accent mario debuted as the player character of donkey kong a 1981 platform game miyamoto created mario after he was unable to obtain the license to use popeye as the protagonist the graphical limitations of arcade hardware influenced marios design such as his nose mustache and overalls and he was named after nintendo of americas landlord mario segale after donkey kong mario starred in mario bros 1983 its 1985 nintendo entertainment system sequel super mario bros began the successful super mario platformer series charles martinet voiced mario from 1991 to 2023 when he was succeeded by kevin afghani mario has appeared in over 200 video games these include puzzle games such as dr mario roleplaying games such as paper mario and mario luigi and sports games such as mario kart and mario tennis he lacks a set personality and consistent profession allowing him to take on many different roles across the mario franchise mario is often accompanied by a large cast of supporting characters including friends like princess daisy toad and yoshi and rivals like bowser jr donkey kong and wario mario has also appeared in other nintendo properties such as the super smash bros series of crossover fighting games mario is an established pop culture icon and is widely considered the most famous video game character in history his likeness has been featured in merchandise and people and places have been nicknamed after him he inspired many video game characters including segas sonic the hedgehog and unofficial media the mario franchise is the bestselling video game franchise of all time with more than 800 million units sold worldwide mario has been adapted in various media he was portrayed by bob hoskins in the liveaction film super mario bros 1993 and voiced by chris pratt in the animated film the super mario bros movie 2023

author: @sispacouet
text_translated: nintendo has long been known for its iconic consoles and games but recently their prices have been creeping up to levels that many gamers are finding hard to justify with new consoles and games now costing over 80 usd thats over 100 cad its becoming increasingly difficult to keep up with the costs of gaming especially when the experience feels like its not evolving as much as it should as the cost of living continues to rise from groceries to rent wages arent increasing at the same pace leaving many people with less disposable income to spend on things like entertainment gaming once an affordable hobby is now becoming a luxury and when that entertainment is priced so high its often the first thing to get cut from the budget its tough to justify spending over 100 cad on a game especially when it feels like the same experiences are being rehashed instead of offering something truly new and exciting for many this pricing model simply doesnt align with whats being delivered the days of affordable gaming are becoming a distant memory and the lack of real innovation in many of the titles makes it harder to justify the increasing costs as people adjust their spending habits due to rising costs in other areas it seems only fair to expect that entertainment especially gaming should reflect the changing realities of the average consumer until that happens cutting back on gaming may be a necessary decision no matter how much we love the nintendo brand

author: @virtualProspector
text_translated: as a dedicated pc gamer who has spent countless hours on steam ive never given the nintendo switch much thought until the recent release of the nintendo switch 2 piqued my interest however upon closer inspection of your business strategy and game pricing i find myself hesitant to make the switch one of the primary issues i have is with the nintendo online subscription service even with the expansion pack it doesnt grant access to any games im still required to purchase each game individually at a hefty price of 70 each for someone like me that translates to only being able to afford two games every other month even if i were to save up the 450 entry cost for older players like myself is a significant barrier i see many older adults in my building enjoying their switch consoles and im particularly interested in playing your renowned zelda franchise however the prospect of having to buy each game at 70 or even 90 for a physical copy of the new mario game is simply outrageous its important to remember that a large portion of your audience is no longer comprised of children they are adults with fulltime jobs and disposable income many of them can easily afford a steam deck oled with 1tb of storage for 650 which boasts a fully functional operating system that can even be used as a desktop in contrast the nintendo switch 2 lacks basic features like a web browser and youre even considering charging for a chat feature it begs the question are you out of touch with the current gaming industry and the needs of your consumers furthermore the overall value proposition of the nintendo switch 2 seems lacking compared to other gaming platforms the high price of games coupled with the lack of a robust online service and basic features makes it a less appealing option for experienced gamers who are accustomed to more comprehensive and affordable gaming experiences i urge you to reconsider your pricing strategy and business model to better align with the expectations of todays gamers by offering more competitive game prices a more comprehensive online service and essential features you can attract a wider audience and ensure the continued success of the nintendo switch platform

author: @BoyMultiYT
text_translated: btw here is a fan made fnaf story five nights at freddys the fifth night the cold stale air of the abandoned freddy fazbears pizzeria carried a scent of dust decay and something far worsesomething metallic and rotting michael afton clad in a dark hoodie and jeans gripped the handle of a rusted axe his father william afton had given him a mission to dismantle the animatronics and bring him their endoskeletons mike had spent the last four nights surviving dodging the animatronics relentless pursuit but now the hunted had become the hunter he stepped out of the safe room where the axe had been stored and into the dark corridors of the pizzeria where his metallic adversaries lurked freddy fazbear the king falls the first to fall would be the leader freddy fazbears deep menacing chuckle echoed through the halls mike waited near the main stage baiting the bear out as soon as freddy turned the corner eyes glowing white in the darkness mike swung the axe with all his strength the blade crashed into freddys chest sparks flying as metal screeched against metal the animatronic stumbled but mike didnt stop another strike caved in its faceplate a third blow severed its right arm with one final furious swing freddy collapsed to the floor twitching and sparking panting mike pried open freddys back panel yanking out the endoskeleton with brute force step one was complete bonnie the silent stalker mike made his way toward the back halls bonnie the relentless guitarist had been the most aggressive on previous nights always appearing when least expected mike had set a trap in the storage room a pile of loose wires and broken machinery stacked in a corner as predicted bonnie moved silently in the shadows red eyes scanning for his prey mike kicked a loose piece of debris drawing bonnies attention the moment the rabbit lunged mike sidestepped sending the animatronic toppling into the scrap heap the tangled wires wrapped around bonnies limbs as he struggled mike wasted no time swinging his axe at the exposed servos in bonnies joints sparks erupted as bonnies limbs gave out his heavy body collapsing into the junk heap with careful precision mike dismantled the rabbit prying out the endoskeleton from its casing two down chica the deceiver the kitchen was the next stop chica with her horrifying gaping beak had always been deceptive lulling her victims into a false sense of security before striking mike knew she would use her damaged voice box to play tricks mimicking human sounds as he entered the room was eerily silentuntil he heard a faint whisper help me mike knew better he stayed still gripping the axe tightly then in a flash of yellow chica lunged from the shadows she moved faster than the others but mike had anticipated her attack he ducked just in time swinging the axe low striking her leg chica stumbled and mike followed up with a devastating blow to her torso tearing through wires and mechanical ribs with brutal efficiency he tore out her endoskeleton leaving the oncefeared animatronic in pieces foxy the hunter becomes the hunted the final target was the fastest and most cunning foxy the pirate had always been an outlier he hid in pirate cove emerging only when least expected mike knew that if he tried to fight foxy headon he would lose instead he lured foxy out he left a trail of scattered endoskeleton parts leading to the arcade where a puddle of spilled cleaning fluid covered the floor hiding behind a cabinet he waited foxy sprinted at full speed claws ready to tear into fleshuntil his foot hit the slick surface the pirate animatronic skidded losing balance and slammed into the wall with a metallic crunch mike emerged and brought the axe down on foxys head cracking the casing the animatronic twitched its eye flickering one final swing foxy was down mike yanked out the last endoskeleton breathing heavily it was done golden freddy the specter as he gathered the endoskeletons the air grew cold the lights flickered mike turned and there it was golden freddy not like the others a lifeless suit slumped overyet its empty sockets bore into him the room warped reality bending as a whisper filled his mind its him then in a blink it was gone the message was clear he had done his fathers bidding but somethingsomeonewas watching the fate of william afton that night mike sat at home unaware of his fathers fate meanwhile william afton stood in the safe room his expression unreadable he had succeeded in his plan or so he thought the spirits appeared before himfour at first he remained composed arms crossed watching them with cold indifference then the fifth spirit materialized williams smirk vanished his body stiffened and for the first time fear took hold the spirits surged forward sending him staggering backwardonce twice three timesuntil he hit the wall panting desperation flickered in his eyes he sneered at them then turned to the old spring bonnie suit a twisted idea formed in his mind slowly deliberately he stepped toward it and began climbing inside you want a reminder he taunted his voice laced with amusement fine let me show you who i really am he let out a chilling laugh as he pulled the headpiece down thena single water droplet fell from the ceiling landing inside the suit the snap of the springlocks echoed through the room williams laughter turned into a guttural agonized scream as the metal clamps crushed him from the inside blood seeped through the seams of the suit as his body convulsed violently before going still the spirits watched in silence their justice was served a new chapter begins in the dimly lit office of a new establishment a photograph sat on a desk a picture of two men william afton and henry emily a new location was coming to be continued
